{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":381,"text":"Let me tell you, it has been a fantastic month for deception."},{"time":4094,"text":"And I'm not even talking about the American presidential race. (Laughter)"},{"time":8347,"text":"We have a high-profile journalist caught for plagiarism,"},{"time":12682,"text":"a young superstar writer whose book involves"},{"time":15614,"text":"so many made up quotes that they've pulled it from the shelves;"},{"time":18919,"text":"a New York Times expos√© on fake book reviews."},{"time":21517,"text":"It's been fantastic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22926,"text":"Now, of course, not all deception hits the news."},{"time":26777,"text":"Much of the deception is everyday. In fact, a lot of research"},{"time":30456,"text":"shows that we all lie once or twice a day, as Dave suggested."},{"time":34787,"text":"So it's about 6:30 now, suggests that most of us should have lied."},{"time":37720,"text":"Let's take a look at Winnipeg. How many of you,"},{"time":39620,"text":"in the last 24 hours -- think back -- have told a little fib,"},{"time":42547,"text":"or a big one? How many have told a little lie out there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46098,"text":"All right, good. These are all the liars."},{"time":48002,"text":"Make sure you pay attention to them. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51295,"text":"No, that looked good, it was about two thirds of you."},{"time":53441,"text":"The other third didn't lie, or perhaps forgot,"},{"time":56293,"text":"or you're lying to me about your lying, which is very,"},{"time":58953,"text":"very devious. (Laughter) This fits with a lot of the research,"},{"time":63003,"text":"which suggests that lying is very pervasive."},{"time":66357,"text":"It's this pervasiveness, combined with the centrality"},{"time":70318,"text":"to what it means to be a human, the fact that we can"},{"time":72758,"text":"tell the truth or make something up,"},{"time":74638,"text":"that has fascinated people throughout history."},{"time":77489,"text":"Here we have Diogenes with his lantern."},{"time":80118,"text":"Does anybody know what he was looking for?"},{"time":82798,"text":"A single honest man, and he died without finding one"},{"time":86582,"text":"back in Greece. And we have Confucius in the East"},{"time":89599,"text":"who was really concerned with sincerity,"},{"time":91976,"text":"not only that you walked the walk or talked the talk,"},{"time":95060,"text":"but that you believed in what you were doing."},{"time":98214,"text":"You believed in your principles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100220,"text":"Now my first professional encounter with deception"},{"time":103151,"text":"is a little bit later than these guys, a couple thousand years."},{"time":106614,"text":"I was a customs officer for Canada back in the mid-'90s."},{"time":110413,"text":"Yeah. I was defending Canada's borders."},{"time":113239,"text":"You may think that's a weapon right there. In fact,"},{"time":117021,"text":"that's a stamp. I used a stamp to defend Canada's borders. (Laughter)"},{"time":122051,"text":"Very Canadian of me. I learned a lot about deception"},{"time":125588,"text":"while doing my duty here in customs,"},{"time":128643,"text":"one of which was that most of what I thought I knew about deception was wrong,"},{"time":131527,"text":"and I'll tell you about some of that tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133279,"text":"But even since just 1995, '96, the way we communicate"},{"time":137353,"text":"has been completely transformed. We email, we text,"},{"time":140650,"text":"we skype, we Facebook. It's insane."},{"time":143263,"text":"Almost every aspect of human communication's been changed,"},{"time":146524,"text":"and of course that's had an impact on deception."},{"time":149084,"text":"Let me tell you a little bit about a couple of new deceptions"},{"time":151667,"text":"we've been tracking and documenting."},{"time":154043,"text":"They're called the Butler, the Sock Puppet"},{"time":158287,"text":"and the Chinese Water Army."},{"time":160368,"text":"It sounds a little bit like a weird book,"},{"time":162265,"text":"but actually they're all new types of lies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164398,"text":"Let's start with the Butlers. Here's an example of one:"},{"time":167443,"text":"\"On my way.\" Anybody ever written, \"On my way?\""},{"time":170556,"text":"Then you've also lied. (Laughter)"},{"time":174319,"text":"We're never on our way. We're thinking about going on our way."},{"time":178516,"text":"Here's another one: \"Sorry I didn't respond to you earlier."},{"time":181279,"text":"My battery was dead.\" Your battery wasn't dead."},{"time":183244,"text":"You weren't in a dead zone."},{"time":185120,"text":"You just didn't want to respond to that person that time."},{"time":187073,"text":"Here's the last one: You're talking to somebody,"},{"time":188870,"text":"and you say, \"Sorry, got work, gotta go.\""},{"time":191360,"text":"But really, you're just bored. You want to talk to somebody else."},{"time":195157,"text":"Each of these is about a relationship,"},{"time":197573,"text":"and this is a 24/7 connected world. Once you get my cell phone number,"},{"time":201978,"text":"you can literally be in touch with me 24 hours a day."},{"time":204943,"text":"And so these lies are being used by people"},{"time":207312,"text":"to create a buffer, like the butler used to do,"},{"time":210138,"text":"between us and the connections to everybody else."},{"time":213545,"text":"But they're very special. They use ambiguity"},{"time":215252,"text":"that comes from using technology. You don't know"},{"time":217313,"text":"where I am or what I'm doing or who I'm with."},{"time":220261,"text":"And they're aimed at protecting the relationships."},{"time":222752,"text":"These aren't just people being jerks. These are people"},{"time":225333,"text":"that are saying, look, I don't want to talk to you now,"},{"time":227709,"text":"or I didn't want to talk to you then, but I still care about you."},{"time":230133,"text":"Our relationship is still important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232533,"text":"Now, the Sock Puppet, on the other hand,"},{"time":234047,"text":"is a totally different animal. The sock puppet isn't"},{"time":236390,"text":"about ambiguity, per se. It's about identity."},{"time":239455,"text":"Let me give you a very recent example,"},{"time":241457,"text":"as in, like, last week."},{"time":242971,"text":"Here's R.J. Ellory, best-seller author in Britain."},{"time":246239,"text":"Here's one of his bestselling books."},{"time":248259,"text":"Here's a reviewer online, on Amazon."},{"time":251672,"text":"My favorite, by Nicodemus Jones, is,"},{"time":254329,"text":"\"Whatever else it might do, it will touch your soul.\""},{"time":258137,"text":"And of course, you might suspect"},{"time":259540,"text":"that Nicodemus Jones is R.J. Ellory."},{"time":262167,"text":"He wrote very, very positive reviews about himself. Surprise, surprise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266854,"text":"Now this Sock Puppet stuff isn't actually that new."},{"time":270114,"text":"Walt Whitman also did this back in the day,"},{"time":273281,"text":"before there was Internet technology. Sock Puppet"},{"time":276336,"text":"becomes interesting when we get to scale,"},{"time":279104,"text":"which is the domain of the Chinese Water Army."},{"time":281622,"text":"Chinese Water Army refers to thousands of people"},{"time":284058,"text":"in China that are paid small amounts of money"},{"time":287106,"text":"to produce content. It could be reviews. It could be"},{"time":290140,"text":"propaganda. The government hires these people,"},{"time":292699,"text":"companies hire them, all over the place."},{"time":295327,"text":"In North America, we call this Astroturfing,"},{"time":298944,"text":"and Astroturfing is very common now. There's a lot of concerns about it."},{"time":302382,"text":"We see this especially with product reviews, book reviews,"},{"time":305609,"text":"everything from hotels to whether that toaster is a good toaster or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310404,"text":"Now, looking at these three reviews, or these three types of deception,"},{"time":314322,"text":"you might think, wow, the Internet is really making us"},{"time":317059,"text":"a deceptive species, especially when you think about"},{"time":320268,"text":"the Astroturfing, where we can see deception brought up to scale."},{"time":324870,"text":"But actually, what I've been finding is very different from that."},{"time":329608,"text":"Now, let's put aside the online anonymous sex chatrooms,"},{"time":332857,"text":"which I'm sure none of you have been in."},{"time":334756,"text":"I can assure you there's deception there."},{"time":337085,"text":"And let's put aside the Nigerian prince who's emailed you"},{"time":339794,"text":"about getting the 43 million out of the country. (Laughter)"},{"time":343022,"text":"Let's forget about that guy, too."},{"time":344702,"text":"Let's focus on the conversations between our friends"},{"time":347646,"text":"and our family and our coworkers and our loved ones."},{"time":349793,"text":"Those are the conversations that really matter."},{"time":352201,"text":"What does technology do to deception with those folks?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356441,"text":"Here's a couple of studies. One of the studies we do"},{"time":359516,"text":"are called diary studies, in which we ask people to record"},{"time":362887,"text":"all of their conversations and all of their lies for seven days,"},{"time":366453,"text":"and what we can do then is calculate how many lies took place"},{"time":369558,"text":"per conversation within a medium, and the finding"},{"time":372506,"text":"that we get that surprises people the most is that email"},{"time":375030,"text":"is the most honest of those three media."},{"time":378309,"text":"And it really throws people for a loop because we think,"},{"time":380710,"text":"well, there's no nonverbal cues, so why don't you lie more?"},{"time":384446,"text":"The phone, in contrast, the most lies."},{"time":388750,"text":"Again and again and again we see the phone is the device"},{"time":390696,"text":"that people lie on the most, and perhaps because of the Butler Lie ambiguities I was telling you about."},{"time":395414,"text":"This tends to be very different from what people expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399389,"text":"What about r√©sum√©s? We did a study in which we had"},{"time":402613,"text":"people apply for a job, and they could apply for a job"},{"time":405157,"text":"either with a traditional paper r√©sum√©, or on LinkedIn,"},{"time":408671,"text":"which is a social networking site like Facebook,"},{"time":411493,"text":"but for professionals -- involves the same information as a r√©sum√©."},{"time":415060,"text":"And what we found, to many people's surprise,"},{"time":417674,"text":"was that those LinkedIn r√©sum√©s were more honest"},{"time":420469,"text":"on the things that mattered to employers, like your"},{"time":422293,"text":"responsibilities or your skills at your previous job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426444,"text":"How about Facebook itself?"},{"time":428740,"text":"You know, we always think that hey, there are these"},{"time":430622,"text":"idealized versions, people are just showing the best things"},{"time":432751,"text":"that happened in their lives. I've thought that many times."},{"time":435407,"text":"My friends, no way they can be that cool and have good of a life."},{"time":438475,"text":"Well, one study tested this by examining people's personalities."},{"time":442296,"text":"They had four good friends of a person judge their personality."},{"time":446514,"text":"Then they had strangers, many strangers,"},{"time":448470,"text":"judge the person's personality just from Facebook,"},{"time":450998,"text":"and what they found was those judgments of the personality"},{"time":453427,"text":"were pretty much identical, highly correlated,"},{"time":455936,"text":"meaning that Facebook profiles really do reflect our actual personality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460309,"text":"All right, well, what about online dating?"},{"time":462881,"text":"I mean, that's a pretty deceptive space."},{"time":464381,"text":"I'm sure you all have \"friends\" that have used online dating. (Laughter)"},{"time":467916,"text":"And they would tell you about that guy that had no hair"},{"time":469974,"text":"when he came, or the woman that didn't look at all like her photo."},{"time":473004,"text":"Well, we were really interested in it, and so what we did"},{"time":476140,"text":"is we brought people, online daters, into the lab,"},{"time":479247,"text":"and then we measured them. We got their height"},{"time":480727,"text":"up against the wall, we put them on a scale, got their weight --"},{"time":484608,"text":"ladies loved that -- and then we actually got their driver's license to get their age."},{"time":488503,"text":"And what we found was very, very interesting."},{"time":492814,"text":"Here's an example of the men and the height."},{"time":496743,"text":"Along the bottom is how tall they said they were in their profile."},{"time":499213,"text":"Along the y-axis, the vertical axis, is how tall they actually were."},{"time":504075,"text":"That diagonal line is the truth line. If their dot's on it,"},{"time":507151,"text":"they were telling exactly the truth."},{"time":508705,"text":"Now, as you see, most of the little dots are below the line."},{"time":511818,"text":"What it means is all the guys were lying about their height."},{"time":514685,"text":"In fact, they lied about their height about nine tenths of an inch,"},{"time":517626,"text":"what we say in the lab as \"strong rounding up.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":523902,"text":"You get to 5'8\" and one tenth, and boom! 5'9\"."},{"time":528405,"text":"But what's really important here is, look at all those dots."},{"time":530403,"text":"They are clustering pretty close to the truth. What we found"},{"time":532969,"text":"was 80 percent of our participants did indeed lie"},{"time":535377,"text":"on one of those dimensions, but they always lied by a little bit."},{"time":538972,"text":"One of the reasons is pretty simple. If you go to a date,"},{"time":541996,"text":"a coffee date, and you're completely different than what you said,"},{"time":545597,"text":"game over. Right? So people lied frequently, but they lied"},{"time":549216,"text":"subtly, not too much. They were constrained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552685,"text":"Well, what explains all these studies? What explains the fact"},{"time":555572,"text":"that despite our intuitions, mine included,"},{"time":560207,"text":"a lot of online communication, technologically-mediated"},{"time":563736,"text":"communication, is more honest than face to face?"},{"time":567764,"text":"That really is strange. How do we explain this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570253,"text":"Well, to do that, one thing is we can look at the deception-detection literature."},{"time":573632,"text":"It's a very old literature by now, it's coming up on 50 years."},{"time":577977,"text":"It's been reviewed many times. There's been thousands of trials,"},{"time":580639,"text":"hundreds of studies, and there's some really compelling findings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584620,"text":"The first is, we're really bad at detecting deception,"},{"time":587856,"text":"really bad. Fifty-four percent accuracy on average when you have to tell"},{"time":591972,"text":"if somebody that just said a statement is lying or not."},{"time":595356,"text":"That's really bad. Why is it so bad?"},{"time":598548,"text":"Well it has to do with Pinocchio's nose."},{"time":601078,"text":"If I were to ask you guys, what do you rely on"},{"time":603437,"text":"when you're looking at somebody and you want to find out"},{"time":605682,"text":"if they're lying? What cue do you pay attention to?"},{"time":608612,"text":"Most of you would say that one of the cues you look at"},{"time":611042,"text":"is the eyes. The eyes are the window to the soul."},{"time":613770,"text":"And you're not alone. Around the world, almost every culture,"},{"time":616173,"text":"one of the top cues is eyes. But the research"},{"time":619036,"text":"over the last 50 years says there's actually no reliable cue"},{"time":622860,"text":"to deception, which blew me away, and it's one of"},{"time":625857,"text":"the hard lessons that I learned when I was customs officer."},{"time":628212,"text":"The eyes do not tell us whether somebody's lying or not."},{"time":630642,"text":"Some situations, yes -- high stakes, maybe their pupils dilate,"},{"time":633660,"text":"their pitch goes up, their body movements change a little bit,"},{"time":637164,"text":"but not all the time, not for everybody, it's not reliable."},{"time":641996,"text":"Strange. The other thing is that just because you can't see me"},{"time":645374,"text":"doesn't mean I'm going to lie. It's common sense,"},{"time":647793,"text":"but one important finding is that we lie for a reason."},{"time":650700,"text":"We lie to protect ourselves or for our own gain"},{"time":653067,"text":"or for somebody else's gain."},{"time":655894,"text":"So there are some pathological liars, but they make up"},{"time":657824,"text":"a tiny portion of the population. We lie for a reason."},{"time":661337,"text":"Just because people can't see us doesn't mean"},{"time":662968,"text":"we're going to necessarily lie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665239,"text":"But I think there's actually something much more"},{"time":666792,"text":"interesting and fundamental going on here. The next big"},{"time":670066,"text":"thing for me, the next big idea, we can find by going"},{"time":673863,"text":"way back in history to the origins of language."},{"time":677002,"text":"Most linguists agree that we started speaking somewhere"},{"time":680889,"text":"between 50,000 and 100,000 years ago. That's a long time ago."},{"time":684057,"text":"A lot of humans have lived since then."},{"time":686673,"text":"We've been talking, I guess, about fires and caves"},{"time":689096,"text":"and saber-toothed tigers. I don't know what they talked about,"},{"time":692203,"text":"but they were doing a lot of talking, and like I said,"},{"time":694721,"text":"there's a lot of humans evolving speaking,"},{"time":697266,"text":"about 100 billion people in fact."},{"time":700072,"text":"What's important though is that writing only emerged"},{"time":702854,"text":"about 5,000 years ago. So what that means is that"},{"time":706441,"text":"all the people before there was any writing,"},{"time":708833,"text":"every word that they ever said, every utterance"},{"time":714419,"text":"disappeared. No trace. Evanescent. Gone."},{"time":719171,"text":"So we've been evolving to talk in a way in which"},{"time":723236,"text":"there is no record. In fact, even the next big change"},{"time":729153,"text":"to writing was only 500 years ago now,"},{"time":731621,"text":"with the printing press, which is very recent in our past,"},{"time":734000,"text":"and literacy rates remained incredibly low right up until World War II,"},{"time":738242,"text":"so even the people of the last two millennia,"},{"time":741626,"text":"most of the words they ever said -- poof! -- disappeared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746658,"text":"Let's turn to now, the networked age."},{"time":750249,"text":"How many of you have recorded something today?"},{"time":754961,"text":"Anybody do any writing today? Did anybody write a word?"},{"time":758138,"text":"It looks like almost every single person here recorded something."},{"time":762364,"text":"In this room, right now, we've probably recorded more"},{"time":765412,"text":"than almost all of human pre-ancient history."},{"time":769954,"text":"That is crazy. We're entering this amazing period"},{"time":773184,"text":"of flux in human evolution where we've evolved to speak"},{"time":777199,"text":"in a way in which our words disappear, but we're in"},{"time":779900,"text":"an environment where we're recording everything."},{"time":782803,"text":"In fact, I think in the very near future, it's not just"},{"time":785140,"text":"what we write that will be recorded, everything we do"},{"time":787489,"text":"will be recorded."},{"time":789822,"text":"What does that mean? What's the next big idea from that?"},{"time":794278,"text":"Well, as a social scientist, this is the most amazing thing"},{"time":798528,"text":"I have ever even dreamed of. Now, I can look at"},{"time":802075,"text":"all those words that used to, for millennia, disappear."},{"time":805686,"text":"I can look at lies that before were said and then gone."},{"time":809934,"text":"You remember those Astroturfing reviews that we were"},{"time":813454,"text":"talking about before? Well, when they write a fake review,"},{"time":816957,"text":"they have to post it somewhere, and it's left behind for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819661,"text":"So one thing that we did, and I'll give you an example of"},{"time":822096,"text":"looking at the language, is we paid people"},{"time":824591,"text":"to write some fake reviews. One of these reviews is fake."},{"time":828126,"text":"The person never was at the James Hotel."},{"time":830069,"text":"The other review is real. The person stayed there."},{"time":832991,"text":"Now, your task now is to decide"},{"time":836518,"text":"which review is fake?"},{"time":840591,"text":"I'll give you a moment to read through them."},{"time":844777,"text":"But I want everybody to raise their hand at some point."},{"time":847064,"text":"Remember, I study deception. I can tell if you don't raise your hand."},{"time":851295,"text":"All right, how many of you believe that A is the fake?"},{"time":857894,"text":"All right. Very good. About half."},{"time":860036,"text":"And how many of you think that B is?"},{"time":863651,"text":"All right. Slightly more for B."},{"time":866180,"text":"Excellent. Here's the answer."},{"time":868772,"text":"B is a fake. Well done second group. You dominated the first group. (Laughter)"},{"time":875353,"text":"You're actually a little bit unusual. Every time we demonstrate this,"},{"time":878199,"text":"it's usually about a 50-50 split, which fits"},{"time":880945,"text":"with the research, 54 percent. Maybe people here"},{"time":883591,"text":"in Winnipeg are more suspicious and better at figuring it out."},{"time":887361,"text":"Those cold, hard winters, I love it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890049,"text":"All right, so why do I care about this?"},{"time":893103,"text":"Well, what I can do now with my colleagues in computer science"},{"time":896371,"text":"is we can create computer algorithms that can analyze"},{"time":899603,"text":"the linguistic traces of deception."},{"time":902503,"text":"Let me highlight a couple of things here"},{"time":904336,"text":"in the fake review. The first is that liars tend to think"},{"time":907779,"text":"about narrative. They make up a story:"},{"time":909367,"text":"Who? And what happened? And that's what happened here."},{"time":912553,"text":"Our fake reviewers talked about who they were with"},{"time":914842,"text":"and what they were doing. They also used the first person singular, I,"},{"time":919607,"text":"way more than the people that actually stayed there."},{"time":922076,"text":"They were inserting themselves into the hotel review,"},{"time":926772,"text":"kind of trying to convince you they were there."},{"time":928468,"text":"In contrast, the people that wrote the reviews that were actually there,"},{"time":932483,"text":"their bodies actually entered the physical space,"},{"time":934915,"text":"they talked a lot more about spatial information."},{"time":937814,"text":"They said how big the bathroom was, or they said,"},{"time":940331,"text":"you know, here's how far shopping is from the hotel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944851,"text":"Now, you guys did pretty well. Most people perform at chance at this task."},{"time":949012,"text":"Our computer algorithm is very accurate, much more accurate"},{"time":951770,"text":"than humans can be, and it's not going to be accurate all the time."},{"time":955061,"text":"This isn't a deception-detection machine to tell"},{"time":957091,"text":"if your girlfriend's lying to you on text messaging."},{"time":959592,"text":"We believe that every lie now, every type of lie --"},{"time":963156,"text":"fake hotel reviews, fake shoe reviews,"},{"time":966943,"text":"your girlfriend cheating on you with text messaging --"},{"time":969857,"text":"those are all different lies. They're going to have"},{"time":971362,"text":"different patterns of language. But because everything's"},{"time":974221,"text":"recorded now, we can look at all of those kinds of lies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978910,"text":"Now, as I said, as a social scientist, this is wonderful."},{"time":982903,"text":"It's transformational. We're going to be able to learn"},{"time":984990,"text":"so much more about human thought and expression,"},{"time":988792,"text":"about everything from love to attitudes,"},{"time":993190,"text":"because everything is being recorded now, but"},{"time":995150,"text":"what does it mean for the average citizen?"},{"time":997554,"text":"What does it mean for us in our lives?"},{"time":1000356,"text":"Well, let's forget deception for a bit. One of the big ideas,"},{"time":1004029,"text":"I believe, is that we're leaving these huge traces behind."},{"time":1007717,"text":"My outbox for email is massive,"},{"time":1010933,"text":"and I never look at it. I write all the time,"},{"time":1014270,"text":"but I never look at my record, at my trace."},{"time":1017708,"text":"And I think we're going to see a lot more of that,"},{"time":1019275,"text":"where we can reflect on who we are by looking at"},{"time":1022436,"text":"what we wrote, what we said, what we did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026054,"text":"Now, if we bring it back to deception, there's a couple"},{"time":1028326,"text":"of take-away things here."},{"time":1030303,"text":"First, lying online can be very dangerous, right?"},{"time":1034791,"text":"Not only are you leaving a record for yourself on your machine,"},{"time":1037497,"text":"but you're leaving a record on the person that you were lying to,"},{"time":1041772,"text":"and you're also leaving them around for me to analyze"},{"time":1043532,"text":"with some computer algorithms."},{"time":1044986,"text":"So by all means, go ahead and do that, that's good."},{"time":1048159,"text":"But when it comes to lying and what we want to do"},{"time":1052313,"text":"with our lives, I think we can go back to"},{"time":1054866,"text":"Diogenes and Confucius. And they were less concerned"},{"time":1058615,"text":"about whether to lie or not to lie, and more concerned about"},{"time":1061447,"text":"being true to the self, and I think this is really important."},{"time":1064732,"text":"Now, when you are about to say or do something,"},{"time":1068915,"text":"we can think, do I want this to be part of my legacy,"},{"time":1073475,"text":"part of my personal record?"},{"time":1076188,"text":"Because in the digital age we live in now,"},{"time":1078845,"text":"in the networked age, we are all leaving a record."},{"time":1083309,"text":"Thank you so much for your time,"},{"time":1085004,"text":"and good luck with your record. (Applause)"}]}]}